50\times 0.3=15
75\times 0.6=45
100\times 0.7=70
P(\mbox{one woman resigns})=\displaystyle\frac{15+45+70}{50+75+100}=\frac{130}{225}.
P(\mbox{one woman resigns and the woman is from Store C})=\displaystyle\frac{70}{50+75+100}=\frac{70}{225}.
P(\mbox{the woman is from Store C}|\mbox{one woman resigns})
=\displaystyle\frac{P(\mbox{one woman resigns and the woman is from Store C})}{P(\mbox{one woman resigns})}=\frac{\frac{70}{225}}{\frac{130}{225}}=\frac{7}{13}.
